  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Peel the <strong>butternut squash </strong>and cut into quarters, lengthways, using a sharp knife</p><p>Tip: Drizzle the knife with a little vegetable oil for easier chopping</p><p>Scoop out the seeds with a spoon and discard, then slice finely</p><p>Add to a<strong> foil</strong>-lined<strong> </strong>baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong>, the <strong>cayenne pepper</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and a pinch of<strong> salt</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1602077287925-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1602077287925-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1602077287925-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1602077287925-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1602077287925-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Give everything a good mix up then put the tray in the oven for 15-20 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Meanwhile, peel and slice the <strong>brown onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Heat a wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) over a high heat with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced onions </strong>with a pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and cook for 8-10 min or until browned</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1602077438850-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1602077438850-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
